Proto-Mediterranean Sea and north eastern Atlantic.
Conilithes antidiluvianus ( Bruguière, 1792 )
sensu stricto occurs in the Tortonian of Italy (Sant'Agata Fossili, Stazzano, Montegibbio) ( Sacco 1893a ; Davoli 1972 ) and becomes very common at Pliocene localities in Italy ( Hall 1966 ; Davoli 1972 ;
Janssen et al . 2014
). Further Pliocene occurrences are mentioned from southern France (Biot), the Hatay Basin in Turkey, Sicily and Syria ( Erünal-Erentöz 1958 ;
Janssen et al . 2014
) (see Robba 1968 for further occurrences).
